*mod_fcgid-2.1-r2 (29 Jul 2007)

  29 Jul 2007; Benedikt Böhm <hollow@gentoo.org>
  -files/mod_fcgid-2.1-apr_shm_remove.patch, -files/20_mod_fcgid-2.1.conf,
  files/20_mod_fcgid.conf, -mod_fcgid-2.0.ebuild, +mod_fcgid-2.1-r2.ebuild:
  remove useless patches; fix configuration file; depend on apache 2.2 because
  apr-1 is needed

  24 May 2007; Christian Heim <phreak@gentoo.org> mod_fcgid-2.1-r1.ebuild:
  Fix the Makefile to use the proper location for our builddir
  (/usr/local/apache2 vs. /usr/$(get_libdir)/apache2), thanks to Samir M.
  Nassar <bugzilla at steamedpenguin.com> in #179597.

*mod_fcgid-2.1-r1 (23 May 2007)

  23 May 2007; Christian Heim <phreak@gentoo.org>
  +files/20_mod_fcgid-2.1.conf, -mod_fcgid-2.1.ebuild,
  +mod_fcgid-2.1-r1.ebuild:
  Revision bump, fixing mod_fcgid w/ apache-2.2.4; as we stopped installing
  /usr/$(get_libdir)/apache2/logs with 2.2.4, the module fails to put its
  socket into the "default" place (definded in mod_fcgid.c as
  DEFAULT_SOCKET_PREFIX and DEFAULT_SHM_PATH). Thanks to Victor Roman
  Archidona <daijo at daijo.org> in #178407.

  14 Mar 2007; Christian Heim <phreak@gentoo.org>
  +files/mod_fcgid-2.1-apr_shm_remove.patch, mod_fcgid-2.1.ebuild:
  Finally fixing #170352, thanks to Xavier again (for pointing me at the
  upstream patch, that removed the weird apr_shm_remove stuff).

  13 Mar 2007; Christian Heim <phreak@gentoo.org> mod_fcgid-2.1.ebuild:
  Looks like newer fcgid needs a newer version of apr, thus forcing
  dev-libs/apr-1*. Thanks to Xavier Neys in #170352.

